# Project Rules — Neuro-Salesman (TG + Web MVP)

## 1) Product Scope (Do/Don’t)
- MVP каналы: ONLY Telegram + Web.
- Цель: лид → (1–3 уточняющих вопроса) → запись/заявка через Web.
- Если Telegram недоступен/ошибка доставки → ALWAYS fallback на Web (ссылка).
- Do NOT: диагнозы, гарантии результата, “лечим/вылечим”, мед.обещания.
- Do NOT: VK/MAX/оплаты/сложные интеграции до завершения MVP.

## 2) One-Command Run
- Проект MUST запускаться одной командой:
  - `docker compose up --build` (локально)
  - `docker compose up -d --build` (сервер)
- Никаких ручных скриптов “перед запуском”. Bootstrap выполняется автоматически при старте backend.

## 3) Single .env Policy
- Используем ONE `.env` (единый для локалки и сервера).
- Различия dev/prod задаются только значениями env или переопределением переменных при запуске.
- `.env` всегда в `.gitignore`. Репозиторий содержит `.env.example` без секретов.

## 4) Container Policy
- Docker Compose сервисы: db (Postgres), backend (FastAPI), frontend (React/Vite).
- Внутри docker сети доступ к БД по host `db`, NEVER `localhost`.
- Все пути только относительные снаружи и фиксированные внутри контейнеров:
  - DATA_DIR=/app/data
  - seeds mounted to /app/seeds (read-only)
  - rag_md_templates mounted to /app/rag_md_templates (read-only)

## 5) Backend Rules (FastAPI)
- Base API prefix: `/api`.
- Required endpoints:
  - GET `/api/health` -> {"ok": true}
  - GET `/api/config` -> без секретов (app_url, rag_enabled, telegram_mode)
  - Inbox + Conversations + Send message endpoints
  - CRUD: kb_articles, offers, reply_templates
  - POST `/api/web/leads`
- Telegram webhook endpoint MUST be: POST `{TELEGRAM_WEBHOOK_PATH}` (default `/integrations/telegram/webhook`) and MUST NOT be under `/api`.
- CORS:
  - allow http://localhost:5173 in dev
  - allow APP_URL in prod

## 6) Telegram Modes
- Mode selection:
  - if `TELEGRAM_WEBHOOK_URL` is non-empty -> webhook mode
  - else -> polling mode
- Mutual exclusivity: webhook mode MUST NOT start polling.
- Polling MUST run as background task and MUST NOT block FastAPI.
- If webhook mode is active: backend MUST call Telegram `setWebhook` on startup and log result.

## 7) Bootstrap & Idempotency (Critical)
- RAG_ENABLED must default to `false` (safe default).
On backend startup:
1) Check DB connection
2) Create tables (SQLAlchemy create_all) and pgvector extension if possible
3) Load seeds from `/app/seeds` idempotently (no duplicates; log import counts)
4) Load Markdown KB from `/app/rag_md_templates` into kb_articles:
   - upsert by front matter `id` if present, else by `title`
5) If `RAG_ENABLED=true`: build embeddings idempotently
   - If embeddings fail, app MUST still start (log error and continue)

## 8) Data Model (Must have)
Tables (or ORM equivalents) required:
- leads, conversations, messages
- lead_status_history, lost_reasons
- kb_articles, offers, reply_templates
- bookings, event_log
Messages must store delivery_status and delivery_error.

## 9) Reply Logic (MVP)
- Default replies are template-based (reply_templates), NOT free chat.
- rules_engine:
  - detect intent (price/booking/address/services/objection_price/doubt/contraindications/other)
  - pick template from DB
  - replace {web_url} = APP_URL + "/web"
- fallback_web template is mandatory and used when delivery fails.
- Compliance guard MUST prevent banned phrases from being auto-sent.

## 10) RAG Policy
- Markdown KB is the source of truth for content.
- Index/search must use KB content; metadata stored separately.
- RAG is optional in MVP via `RAG_ENABLED` and must not break startup.

## 11) Frontend Rules (React/Vite)
- Frontend runs in Docker as Vite dev server:
  - `npm run dev -- --host 0.0.0.0 --port 5173`
- Pages required:
  - "/" Inbox
  - "/lead/:id" Lead card + chat
  - "/web" Public form (create lead)
- Must use `VITE_API_BASE_URL` for API calls.
- Include “Check API” button (calls /health).

## 12) Code Quality & Safety
- No secrets in code or commits.
- Use type hints in Python and basic error handling.
- Log meaningful errors (DB, Telegram delivery, bootstrap).
- Keep implementation minimal; avoid premature optimizations.

## 13) Output Expectations
- Provide full repo structure + README with exact run/test commands.
- The project is “Done” only when it runs via Docker and TG bot + frontend work end-to-end.
